theorem Topology.dense_of_interior_compl_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hInt : interior (Aᶜ) = (∅ : Set X)) : Dense A := by
  -- Step 1:  `(closure A)ᶜ ⊆ interior (Aᶜ)`
  have hSubset : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ interior (Aᶜ) := by
    -- `(closure A)ᶜ` is open…
    have hOpen : IsOpen ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) :=
      isClosed_closure.isOpen_compl
    -- …and contained in `Aᶜ`.
    have hSub : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ (Aᶜ) := by
      intro x hxCompl
      by_cases hxA : x ∈ A
      · have : (x : X) ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
        exact False.elim (hxCompl this)
      · simpa [Set.mem_compl] using hxA
    -- Apply `interior_maximal`.
    exact interior_maximal hSub hOpen
  -- Step 2:  `(closure A)ᶜ = ∅`
  have hComplEmpty : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    ·
      have : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ interior (Aᶜ) := hSubset
      simpa [hInt] using this
    · exact Set.empty_subset _
  -- Step 3:  `closure A = univ`
  have hClosure : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    have : closure A = (((closure A)ᶜ : Set X)ᶜ) := by
      simp
    simpa [hComplEmpty, Set.compl_empty] using this
  -- Step 4:  conclude density.
  exact ⟨hClosure⟩
